    &lt;Title&gt;Awful service &lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I visited today with my brother who has been suffering from abdominal pain. He isn't one to cause a fuss and is a nightmare to try and get to make a doctors appointment never mind go to the hospital however because of the pain he is currently in, I managed to get him to agree to let me take him to hospital today. My brother was taken in for assessment 20 mins after arriving and was advised he needed blood tests before he could see a doctor and was to wait back in the waiting room. After over an hour of waiting for his bloods to be taken I asked at reception how long was the wait. The women on reception ( I didnt get her name) advised that a request hadn't even been put through! She said she would add him to the list, he would then have to wait a further 1.5 hours for his bloods to come back and then however long it would take to see a doctor. No apology or anything! I appreciate that it was very busy but there was no need for how rude she was to me! So we had basically been waiting for over an hour for nothing whilst my brother was sat in pain, he wasnt even offered any pain relief! Needless to say he refused to stay any longer after that and is now back at home in bed! I'm not sure how we are now supposed to get him to agree to go back after the terrible service we received!&lt;/CommentText&gt;
